---

## Why an orchestration methodology (not ad-hoc runs)

Executing the full test matrix requires ~9h realistic / ~31h worst-case
wall-clock spread across multiple sessions. Without a methodology:

- Tests contaminate each other via shared `/tmp/payload.json`.
- Solver logs intermingle — no clear per-test attribution.
- The main conversation context fills up with verbose solver output.
- Re-running a round after a session ends wastes effort.

This methodology isolates each test, preserves per-test reports in a
state doc, and gates rounds so a regression is caught before wasting a
2h solve on the next test.

