## Isolation rules (invariants)

| Shared resource | Isolation mechanism |
|---|---|
| Solver job queue | Semaphore serializes — agents naturally queue. |
| Payload staging file | Each agent uses `/tmp/payload-<TC_ID>.json` (composite uses `-a/-b` suffixes). |
| `planner_output` rows | Keyed by auto-generated `plan_id` (`PLAN-<ts>`). |
| `planner_assignments` rows | Keyed by `plan_id`. |
| Checkpoints | `{job_id}_partition_*.json` — job_id globally unique. |
| Docker logs | Every line carries `job_id`. Agents grep with `--since @$SUBMIT_TS`. |
| State tracker doc | ONLY the main session writes it. Agents return structured reports; main session appends rows. |

**No write path** exists where two agents collide. Read verification
queries use `plan_id` filters.

