## Round gating criteria

| Round | Pass criterion for advancing | If failed |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | Pre-flight checklist fully green. | Stop, fix environment, retry Round 0. |
| 1 | Both TC-01 and TC-02 PASS. | Halt suite — baseline or activation broken. Triage via changelog Phase K (LC-08 gate) or Phase E (LC-06). |
| 2 | ≥3 of 4 tests pass (TC-03..05, TC-10). | Halt for triage; failing test identifies the broken orthogonal path. |
| 3 | ≥3 of 4 tests pass (TC-06..09). | Halt for triage. |
| 4 | All three (N-2, N-3, N-5) pass. | Small stakes — document and continue. |
| 5 | State tracker + validation report written. | N/A (reporting only). |

A "halt" is a **main-session** decision — the user signs off before
continuing.

