## Rollback procedure (if a round exposes a regression)

See the "Rollback" section of the implementation changelog for the
exact file-by-file revert order. Summary:

1. Revert `solver/model.py` LC-08 gate + rest-day row extraction.
2. Revert `constraints/lc_06_rest_days_allocation.py` (remove file).
3. Revert `constraints/lc_05_weekend_frequency.py` return signature.
4. Revert `api/service.py` flag derivation + `_save_results_sync`
   extended params.
5. Keep schema changes — they are forward-compatible.

Do NOT roll back schema migrations mid-suite. They have safe defaults
(`fetch_rt=TRUE`, `fetch_ct=TRUE`, `assignment_type='DEMAND'`) that
preserve legacy behavior.

